01:32.526 --> 01:35.594
Yeah? At least your father
sounds like a smart man.

01:37.364 --> 01:39.364
My father's a dick, sir.

01:39.366 --> 01:42.835
Between work and his unrivaled
enthusiasm for Monday Night Football,

01:43.571 --> 01:45.437
he has no idea what my deal is.

01:48.943 --> 01:50.742
Sorry to bother you.

01:50.744 --> 01:54.813
But Mom said that your
self-indulgent practice interview

01:54.815 --> 01:56.982
can wait until
after dinner. Okay?

01:58.385 --> 02:00.285
Are you going
to take this seriously?

02:00.287 --> 02:03.055
I pulled a lot of strings
to get you this job interview.

02:03.057 --> 02:05.591
Do you know what I was doing
the summer after high school?

02:05.593 --> 02:07.493
- Drugs?
- That's not funny.

02:07.495 --> 02:11.997
Hey everyone, I, uh... I have
a lot more in the car, so...

02:11.999 --> 02:13.065
Just a sec, hon.

02:13.067 --> 02:17.102
I was working 12-hour shifts
in your grandfather's factory.

02:17.104 --> 02:18.837
- And do you know why?
- Because he forced you?

02:18.839 --> 02:20.506
He was preparing me
for the future.

02:20.508 --> 02:22.741
He knew one day I'd take over.

02:22.743 --> 02:26.411
Well, I'm sorry I don't have your unbridled
passion for the ketchup industry, Dad.

02:26.413 --> 02:28.647
It's like, I don't want to live in
the same town I grew up in forever.

02:28.649 --> 02:29.915
None of us want that.

02:29.917 --> 02:31.350
Will you shut up, Lib?

02:31.352 --> 02:34.319
Guys? I really could use a hand.

02:34.321 --> 02:35.754
Yeah, just a second.

02:37.525 --> 02:39.625
I don't think a summer job
is too much to ask.

02:39.627 --> 02:43.529
You know, Ritchie's daughter, Kelly,
waits tables to help pay for college

02:43.531 --> 02:44.963
and she's still
graduating early.

02:44.965 --> 02:46.698
And with the help
of her brother, Eddie,

02:46.700 --> 02:48.934
they cured cancer
and got the Huns out of China.

02:48.936 --> 02:50.435
Eddie's only a sophomore.

02:50.437 --> 02:53.639
He's already on path to get
a full football scholarship.

02:53.641 --> 02:57.376
Wow, sounds like
your ideal son, Dad.

02:57.378 --> 03:01.847
I'm not trying to make
you feel bad. Only motivate you.

03:04.985 --> 03:06.185
I got to get this.

03:06.687 --> 03:08.187
Why is she in a bad mood?

03:08.189 --> 03:09.855
I'm coming!

03:10.291 --> 03:12.157
Mom, why not?

03:12.159 --> 03:14.459
Because I know the kinds of things
that happen on spring break.

03:14.461 --> 03:17.296
What? Kids of overprotective parents
get to reclaim a moment of sanity?

03:17.298 --> 03:19.298
Minors get high and smoke weed.

03:19.300 --> 03:21.200
Well, that's not why I'm going.

03:21.202 --> 03:25.404
Mom, look. Here. See? Culture.

03:26.507 --> 03:28.207
The Starling festival?

03:28.209 --> 03:30.809
Yeah, it's supposed
to be amazing and educational.

03:30.811 --> 03:33.178
- So, it's good.
- Mm-hmm.

03:33.180 --> 03:34.680
Did you ask your father?

03:34.682 --> 03:35.847
He never says yes to anything!

03:35.849 --> 03:37.149
I agree with your mother.

03:37.818 --> 03:39.318
You don't even know
what we're talking about.

03:39.320 --> 03:41.053
This looks amazing, Laura!

03:41.388 --> 03:42.654
Thank you.

03:42.656 --> 03:44.556
- Where's Lib?
- Hunger strike.

03:44.825 --> 03:45.824
Again?

03:45.826 --> 03:47.859
More of Grandma Ruth's pie
for you.

03:47.861 --> 03:49.428
Ooh!

03:50.831 --> 03:52.164
You have our full support.

03:53.534 --> 03:57.269
So, it looks like I have to leave
first thing in the morning for Japan.

03:57.271 --> 03:58.837
Feeling that
three-day itch, huh?

03:58.839 --> 04:01.506
Could you send someone
else this time?

04:01.508 --> 04:02.908
Because the kids
have spring break.

04:02.910 --> 04:05.177
And it would be great
if the whole family could...

04:05.179 --> 04:09.181
Do you think I enjoy being
out of town for weeks on end?

04:09.183 --> 04:13.085
You know, living out of suitcases?
Eating nothing but room service?

04:13.087 --> 04:14.853
I would!

04:16.357 --> 04:18.190
She gets that from
your side of the family.

04:18.192 --> 04:21.560
Okay, well, if Philip wants
to go to the Starling Festival,

04:21.562 --> 04:24.229
then I could take both
of the kids to the lake.

04:24.231 --> 04:25.597
- No!
- No!

04:28.569 --> 04:31.270
Philip has his summer
job interview on Monday.

04:31.272 --> 04:34.573
And, uh... I put in a lot
of effort to make that happen.

04:34.575 --> 04:38.043
How much effort does it take to
hire your son when you're the boss?

04:38.045 --> 04:39.878
You wouldn't understand
the politics, Laura.

04:41.548 --> 04:43.582
- Right.
- No, it's fine, Mom.

04:43.584 --> 04:46.551
I mean, a family vacation is not exactly
what I had in mind for spring break anyhow.

04:46.553 --> 04:49.454
But a bird migration
festival is?

04:50.724 --> 04:53.025
All right. This is BS.

04:54.061 --> 04:55.594
- Philip...
- Where do you think you're going?

04:55.596 --> 04:57.596
To Lewis'. To study.

04:57.598 --> 05:01.233
- That better be reflected in your grades.
- Frank. Frank, let him go.

05:01.235 --> 05:02.801
I hope you're home by 10:00.

05:04.605 --> 05:06.905
Do you remember
when we went to this?

05:06.907 --> 05:07.907
Hmm. No.

06:10.637 --> 06:11.870
Beer me.

06:13.640 --> 06:15.340
Did you speak to your parents?

06:15.342 --> 06:17.142
Did you sell them on the whole

06:17.144 --> 06:19.878
"culture," "science," "festival of
bird migrations" trip for break?

06:19.880 --> 06:22.481
I'm pretty sure they saw it as a
ploy to smoke weed and score girls.

06:22.483 --> 06:23.815
What? Dude, come on.

06:23.817 --> 06:25.550
- It was a terrible idea.
- It was a great idea.

06:25.552 --> 06:27.486
- For who?
- My parents bought it.

06:27.488 --> 06:28.820
Yeah, well, your parents
are idiots, man.

06:28.822 --> 06:30.856
Look, this is
our senior year, dude.

06:30.858 --> 06:33.158
This is our last
spring break ever.

06:33.160 --> 06:36.094
Our final chance to act like the
popular kids we pretend to hate!

06:36.096 --> 06:38.130
You have to inhale.
All the way...

06:38.932 --> 06:40.332
My final chance
to get with Allison.

06:41.535 --> 06:44.836
