never had a chance with Allison.

06:45.539 --> 06:48.940
Shit man, I even got my uncle
to let us crash at his place!

06:48.942 --> 06:50.909
- Is it by the lake?
- It's close enough.

06:51.512 --> 06:53.412
Come on, man. How old are you?

06:55.449 --> 06:57.916
I'm almost 18. I...

06:59.219 --> 07:01.319
Yeah, you know what?
You're right. Okay, I...

07:02.089 --> 07:04.923
I'm tired of my dad telling me
what I can and can't do.

07:04.925 --> 07:07.025
- He's going to Japan, right?
- Mm-hmm.

07:07.027 --> 07:10.862
And then my mom is going to that PETA
demonstration with Lib in the morning.

07:11.565 --> 07:14.733
If we leave before they get
back, we'll be fine.

07:14.735 --> 07:17.202
Hell yeah! Shit.

07:17.204 --> 07:18.970
- We are men. We can do...
- That's right.

07:18.972 --> 07:21.039
There's Sam. Let's go say hi.

07:21.041 --> 07:22.207
Hey Allison!

07:24.211 --> 07:26.611
Don't think she heard me.

07:26.613 --> 07:28.079
You weren't very loud.

07:28.081 --> 07:30.215
- Should I be louder?
- No.

07:49.636 --> 07:51.002
It's way after 10:00.

07:51.004 --> 07:52.737
Can you just ground me
in the morning?

07:52.739 --> 07:54.773
- Did you...
- No, no. Dad, I wasn't drinking.

07:54.775 --> 07:57.509
Did you apply to NYU?

07:57.511 --> 08:00.912
I'm assuming that's one of those
we-regret-to-inform-you letters.

08:00.914 --> 08:03.515
I mean, I... I thought
it'd be a waste of time.

08:03.517 --> 08:04.683
Well...

08:06.253 --> 08:07.253
You got in.

08:14.328 --> 08:16.361
"Dear Philip,
we are pleased to inform you..."

08:16.363 --> 08:19.164
I... I got in.

08:19.166 --> 08:20.298
Holy shit!

08:20.300 --> 08:21.933
I thought you wanted
to go to State.

08:21.935 --> 08:23.635
You want me to go to State.

08:23.637 --> 08:26.771
I wanted to get as far away
from here as possible. That...

08:26.773 --> 08:28.440
I should call Lewis.

08:28.442 --> 08:29.139
Philip.

08:29.151 --> 08:31.276
You're right, it's late.
I should pack, or...

08:31.278 --> 08:32.844
- Philip...
- No, no, wait, wait.

08:32.846 --> 08:34.846
Why would I pack
four months in advance?

08:34.847 --> 08:36.448
That's... Everything
would get wrinkled.

08:36.450 --> 08:38.250
Philip. You can't go.

08:39.686 --> 08:40.655
What do you mean?

08:40.667 --> 08:43.455
Philip, you're not ready
for New York City at all.

08:43.457 --> 08:45.457
Dad, I can't be a musician here.

08:45.459 --> 08:50.862
A musician? Nobody goes to
college to be a musician.

08:50.864 --> 08:52.831
It's not happening. I'm sorry.

08:55.002 --> 08:56.401
No, you're not.

08:56.402 --> 08:57.801
You're thrilled to have another
thing to take away from me.

08:57.804 --> 09:02.040
No NYU, no girlfriend,
you won't even let me have a dog!

09:02.042 --> 09:03.942
Since when did you have
a girlfriend?

09:05.579 --> 09:07.178
I'm almost 18, all right?

09:07.180 --> 09:09.648
You need to stop treating me
like the 5-year-old

09:09.650 --> 09:13.051
who puked on Allison Schumer
at the piano recital.

09:13.053 --> 09:15.142
From what I see,
you're still acting like that kid.

09:15.154 --> 09:16.154
How do you know?

09:16.490 --> 09:18.156
You're never here!

09:32.406 --> 09:33.838
Can I come in?

09:34.942 --> 09:36.508
Legally, I can't stop you.

09:36.510 --> 09:37.842
He'll never let you go.

09:37.844 --> 09:39.578
Maybe I don't need
his permission.

09:39.580 --> 09:42.080
But you need his money.
Tuition isn't cheap.

09:44.518 --> 09:46.017
And you can forget scholarships.

09:46.019 --> 09:47.786
Because you don't exactly
look good on paper.

09:49.289 --> 09:50.956
Okay, aren't you too young
to be hating men?

09:50.958 --> 09:52.891
Look at my role models.

10:23.123 --> 10:24.889
You ready to ditch
this ghost town?

10:24.891 --> 10:26.491
Ah, you have no idea.

10:37.070 --> 10:38.570
If you play that thing
when people are around,

10:38.572 --> 10:40.071
you might actually get laid
once in a while.

10:40.073 --> 10:42.507
Uh, I get laid
all the time, so...

10:42.509 --> 10:44.669
It doesn't count if you're
the only person in the room.

10:46.113 --> 10:48.947
Check it out. Must be getting close.
It's your dad's first baby.

10:48.949 --> 10:51.149
Yeah, the one
he actually spends time with.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.781
But think about all the
parties we could throw there.

10:52.793 --> 10:53.585
Think anyone would come?

10:53.587 --> 10:56.454
All of the ladies
we are gonna hit this weekend!

11:04.665 --> 11:05.830
Yeah!

11:06.933 --> 11:08.366
Spring break!

11:08.368 --> 11:12.604
- Whoa! Yeah.
- Oh, yeah!

11:16.543 --> 11:18.176
Hey, they seem nice.

11:26.687 --> 11:28.019
Is this it?

11:29.189 --> 11:31.056
So much for bachelor paradise.

11:34.327 --> 11:35.694
I think it's nicer
on the inside.

11:35.696 --> 11:37.362
Thank God I got my tetanus shot.

11:40.300 --> 11:41.366
Uncle Ross?

11:45.906 --> 11:47.972
Hello? Uncle... Ross?

11:50.143 --> 11:52.310
Ugh. What time is it?

11:53.180 --> 11:54.212
Daytime.

11:54.648 --> 11:55.914
